%% End-to-end sequence: form submission → confirmed event.
%% Shows the actors, automations, and scripts involved in a happy-path booking.

sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Form as 📝 Booking Form
    participant BR as 📋 Booking Request
    participant AB as 📋 Available Bookings
    actor Staff
    participant Slack as 💬 Slack
    participant Gmail as ✉️ Gmail
    participant GCal as 📅 Google Calendar
    participant SC as 📋 Sandbox Calendar

    User->>Form: Fill out form,<br/>select slots
    Form->>BR: Create record<br/>(External=1, status='new request')

    par form-submit automations
        BR->>Slack: Notification to DFZ channel
        BR->>Gmail: Notification to staff
        BR->>BR: script 04: Flag Clear Out / All Day
    end

    Staff->>BR: Set Booking Status = 'confirmed'

    par confirmation automations
        BR->>AB: script 02 (booking range fill)<br/>Mark each slot in [Start,End)<br/>as Type='Booking'
        BR->>AB: script 03 (setup/teardown/pending)<br/>Apply Setup/Teardown/Pending<br/>to neighboring slots
        BR->>GCal: Create calendar event
        BR->>Gmail: Confirmation email to user
    end

    GCal->>SC: One-way sync<br/>brings event into Airtable
    SC->>BR: Check External lookup length<br/>length = 1 → skip mirror creation

    Note over BR,SC: System remains in steady state<br/>until rejection or event deletion.

    opt If event later deleted in Google Calendar
        GCal--xSC: Event removed via sync
        SC->>BR: Event ID lookup goes empty
        BR->>BR: script 06: orphan-record-cleanup<br/>deletes the Booking Request
    end
